-- Silver Climbs to 30-Year High, Palladium at 9-Year Peak on Dollar Weakness
-- B y   S u n g w o o   P a r k
-- 2010-11-01T00:09:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-01/silver-climbs-to-30-year-high-palladium-at-9-year-peak-on-dollar-weakness.html
Silver for immediate delivery climbed
as much as 1.1 percent to $25.0050 an ounce, the highest price
since 1980 as the weakening dollar increased the appeal of
precious metals as an alternative asset.  Spot palladium gained as much as 0.9 percent to $653.38 an
ounce, the highest level since 2001.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Sungwoo Park  in Seoul at 
 spark47@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
